tructionsLoaded event appeared.\n\n16. I corrected my findings: hooks likely DO fire in subagent contexts but CLOOKS_DEBUG isn't inherited. Many events fire outside tool-call lifecycle and are invisible in conversation context.\n\n17. User asked me to: (a) modify debug-payload.ts to also log to a file, (b) start a subagent to research Claude Code hooks docs.\n\n18. I added file logging to debug-payload.ts using appendFileSync to `.clooks/debug-events.log`.\n\n19. The log file was created and is working - capturing PreToolUse, PostToolUse, PostToolUseFailure events.\n\n20. Research agent is still running in background (35 lines of output so far).\n\nKey findings confirmed:\n- Finding 1: SessionStart missing `permissionMode` (BaseContext says required)\n- Finding 2: `originalToolInput` leaks to PostToolUse/PostToolUseFailure (not in types)\n- Finding 5: WorktreeCreate requires active handler (success+path)\n- Finding 6: debug-payload.ts missing WorktreeCreate handler\n- Finding 7 (corrected): CLOOKS_DEBUG not inherited by subagent tmux panes\n- Several events (Stop, ConfigChange, SubagentStart/Stop, TeammateIdle/TaskCompleted) never observed - might fire outside tool-call lifecycle\n</analysis>\n\n<summary>\n1. Primary Request and Intent:\n   The user wants active debugging of the clooks hook system. With CLOOKS_DEBUG=true and the debug-payload.ts hook active, the task is to trigger each hook event type from within Claude Code, capture the actual payload, and compare it against the expected type definitions in `.clooks/hooks/types.d.ts`. The goal is to verify that the runtime payloads match the source code contracts, find discrepancies, and understand which events actually fire in practice.\n\n2. Key Technical Concepts:\n   - **Clooks hook runtime**: Bash entrypoint → compiled Bun binary → reads clooks.yml → runs TypeScript hooks → aggregates results\n   - **Hook event lifecycle**: Claude Code sends snake_case JSON on stdin → `normalizeKeys()` converts to camelCase → `hookEventName` renamed to `event` → context enriched with `parallel`, `signal`, `originalToolInput` → passed to hook handler\n   - **Event categories**: Guard events (PreToolUse, UserPromptSubmit, PermissionRequest, Stop, SubagentStop, ConfigChange), Observe events (SessionStart, PostToolUse, PostToolUseFailure, Notification, SubagentStart, SessionEnd, InstructionsLoaded, WorktreeRemove, PreCompact), Continuation events (TeammateIdle, TaskCompleted), Special (WorktreeCreate)\n   - **Output channels**: `injectContext` (appears in system-reminder, only for supported events), `debugMessage` (appears in `[clooks:debug]` stderr lines), file logging (newly added)\n   - **beforeHook gate**: debug-payload.ts checks `process.env.CLOOKS_DEBUG !== \"true\"` and skips if unset — this is why subagents in separate tmux panes don't produce debug output\n   - **Key source files for context building**: `src/engine.ts` (stdin parsing, normalization, context construction), `src/normalize.ts` (snake_case → camelCase), `src/types/claude-code.ts` (Claude Code input contract), `src/types/contexts.ts` (Clooks context interfaces), `src/lifecycle.ts` (handler invocation)\n\n3. Files and Code Sections:\n   - **`.clooks/hooks/debug-payload.ts`** — The debug hook that echoes payloads. Was modified to add file logging.\n     - Added `appendFileSync` logging to `.clooks/debug-events.log`\n     - Current state after edit:\n     ```typescript\n     import type { ClooksHook } from \"./types.js\"\n     import type { BaseContext } from \"../../src/types/contexts.js\"\n     import { appendFileSync } from \"node:fs\"\n     import { join } from \"node:path\"\n\n     const LOG_FILE = join(import.meta.dir, \"..\", \"debug-events.log\")\n\n     function dump(ctx: BaseContext): string {\n       const { signal: _, ...rest } = ctx\n       return JSON.stringify(rest, null, 2)\n     }\n\n     function logToFile(ctx: BaseContext): void {\n       const ts = new Date().toISOString()\n       const line = `[${ts}] $