to report on Claude Code hooks documentation to determine which events are actually implemented vs spec-only\n\n6. All user messages:\n   - \"ClooksDebug is on with debug-payload.ts and we have a hook that always outputs whatever payload it gets. It's your turn to do some active debugging. Try triggering each hook with some action here in claude code and see and see if the intput is equal to what we expect in our source code. Maybe use subagents to do your bidding for each hook/test case, as otherwise the context is gonna get quite full\"\n   - \"Do you see the output from clooks?\"\n   - \"Why are they not testable? o_O\"\n   - \"You can just ask me a PermissionRequest. You can try to change the config yourself. does InstructionsLoaded not fire when loading a skill? Do these hooks currently log into a file in debug mode? Teammate Idle/ Completed you can test by just spawning an agent team.\"\n   - \"try writing something to the home. Teammate might not work because it spawns a separate tmux pane - maybe it doesn't inherit CLOOKS_DEBUG=true mode.Maybe the same for subagents? Task completed should be something you could do, you could spawn your own task, no? You should've had several STOP now, maybe they dont get injected here? You can edit config, just... add an extra newline at the end. load any skill, here, I'll load one for you. /design-principles\"\n   - \"Ok. First off, adjust the debug hook so it also logs everything to a file. Start a subagent that looks into `https://code.claude.com/docs/en/hooks#json-output` for those hooks to figure out if that behaviour is expected or not.\"\n\n7. Pending Tasks:\n   - **Research agent still running**: Background agent researching Claude Code hooks documentation at code.claude.com to determine which events are actually implemented. Agent ID: a26cf582658a09f6f, output at /tmp/claude-1000/-opt-development-clooks/tasks/a26cf582658a09f6f.output (35 lines so far, still in progress)\n   - **Verify file logging captures invisible